---

---

<section id="faq" class="faq section-padding">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title font-display">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-content">
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" data-faq="1">
            <span
              >Do I need prior knowledge of Singapore's history or policy?
            </span>
            <div class="faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" data-answer="1">
            <p>
              Not at all! While familiarity may help, all participants will
              receive sufficient context, guidance, and resources during the
              simulation. The event is designed to be accessible to students
              from all backgrounds and levels of experience.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" data-faq="2">
            <span>Do I need MUN or debating experience?</span>
            <div class="faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" data-answer="2">
            <p>
              WWG is designed to be accessible to participants from all
              backgrounds and all levels of experience! As an emerging
              conference with its unique set of Rules of Procedures, all
              participants will receive sufficient context, guidance, and
              resources before and during the simulation.
            </p>
            <p>
              A mini guide will be disseminated to participants which include
              background briefs, tips, and optional readings. There will also be
              a complimentary pre-conference training session to help all
              participants familiarise themselves with the conference
              proceedings, allowing them to feel more confident and prepared for
              the conference itself.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" data-faq="3">
            <span
              >What is the difference between WWG and regular MUN conferences?</span
            >
            <div class="faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" data-answer="3">
            <p>
              WWG is a public policy simulation modelled after Singapore’s
              policymaking process, deriving its Standing Orders from the
              Standing Orders of the Parliament of Singapore. Comparatively, MUN
              conferences are simulations of the United Nations councils and are
              therefore governed by the United Nations Rules of Procedure.
            </p>
            <p>
              Additionally, while topics discussed at MUN conferences typically
              aim to expand participants' knowledge in global affairs and
              historical crises, the topics at WWG address more pertinent local
              issues that resonate more deeply with citizens, empowering
              participants to think critically about shaping our nation’s
              evolving future.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" data-faq="4">
            <span
              >What is the difference between WWG and other moot parliament
              programmes?</span
            >
            <div class="faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="24"
                height="24"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" data-answer="4">
            <p>
              While both try to replicate the Singapore Parliament, WWG focuses
              more on modelling the contentions behind policymaking and how
              different stakeholders contribute to the drafting of policy
              solutions. In contrast, other moot parliament programmes emphasise
              realism through highly rigid and structured rules of procedure,
              formal bill frameworks, and strict adherence to parliamentary
              modelling.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      <div class="faq-contact">
        <div class="contact-card card">
          <div class="contact-content">
            <h3 class="contact-title font-display">Still Have Questions?</h3>
            <p class="contact-description">
              Can't find what you're looking for? We're here to help! Reach out
              to us for any additional questions or clarifications.
            </p>
            <div class="contact-info">
              <strong>Contact us at: events@prepmun.sg</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    background: black;
  }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gray-800);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-question:hover {
    background: var(--gray-50);
  }

  .faq-icon {
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-answer {
    max-height: 500px;
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    color: var(--gray-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .answer-sections {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .answer-section {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .answer-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .answer-section h4 {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gray-800);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .answer-section p {
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--gray-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-contact {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
  }

  .contact-card {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--cream) 0%,
      rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.1) 100%
    );
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gray-800);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .contact-description {
    color: var(--gray-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .contact-info {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .faq-contact {
      position: static;
    }

    .faq-question {
      padding: 1rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .faq-answer p,
    .answer-sections {
      padding: 0 1rem 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const faqQuestions = document.querySelectorAll(".faq-question");

    faqQuestions.forEach((question) => {
      question.addEventListener("click", function () {
        const faqItem = this.closest(".faq-item");
        const isActive = faqItem.classList.contains("active");

        // Close all FAQ items
        document.querySelectorAll(".faq-item").forEach((item) => {
          item.classList.remove("active");
        });

        // Open clicked item if it wasn't active
        if (!isActive) {
          faqItem.classList.add("active");
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>
